Everyone discusses the quality of the port, but not the quality of the game? IMO, the game is pretty boring. Fighting (what you do the entire game) feels robotic; the player has so much health you'll find yourself burning your thumb as you spam away (no reason to do anything else). The story has some fun moments and voice-acting is top-notch, but it doesn't mean anything if gameplay is stale. If you have the money to spend, I'd only suggest this after you try SA or VC, which are more filling.

Controls: The controls are mediocre for a mobile game, it's what you'd expect and it's pretty fun to play.  Graphics: Graphics wise, it's decent but it's lacking a lot of the ambient light in the school, so don't expect beautiful graphics. It's just plain white, and no light coming in from the windows, which makes the game pretty dull and removes any dark spots from the game. The girls dorm, for example is a brightly coloured mess. It's like running a source engine game in fullbright mode.  Gameplay is as good as it is on the Xbox 360 or PS2.  There are also a lot of obvious bugs that occur on my device which if playtested could've been easily swatted. One, for example, which is a common occurrence is getting on a bike and having my screen go completely black unless I reload, or the camera, instead of focusing on Jimmy, goes glitchy and starts rotating horizontally and vertically, flickering if you will.
